Acme-Compress

When used inside a script, Acme::Compress compresses all the code,
making it working normally, but in less space.

Due to the compression algorithm, the compression rate is noticeable only
for very big scripts.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Acme::Compress

You can also look for information at:

    Homepage
        http://alexlog.co.cc/projects/acme-compress

    Git Repository
        http://github.com/AlexBio/Acme-Compress

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Acme-Compress

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Acme-Compress

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Acme-Compress

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Acme-Compress/


